Privacy Policy for almashfa Mobile App

At almashfa, we take the protection of your personal information seriously and are committed to maintaining the privacy of our users. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect the information that we gather through our Android healthcare app.

Information We Collect

We collect personal information from our users when they create an account, log in, or use the app's features. This information includes, but is not limited to, your name, email address, phone number, and medical history. We also collect information about your device, including your device's unique identifier, IP address, and location data.

We also collect information about your use of the app, including the pages and features you access, the content you view, and the actions you take. This information is used to improve the app's performance and provide you with relevant content and features.

Use of Information

The information we collect is used to provide you with the best possible experience when using our app. We use your personal information to create and manage your account, to provide you with personalized content and features, and to communicate with you about your use of the app.

We also use your information to improve the app's performance, to troubleshoot problems, and to ensure the app's security.

Sharing of Information

We may share your information with third parties to provide you with the best possible service. This includes sharing your information with our partners and service providers, such as our healthcare providers, to provide you with relevant content and features.

We may also share your information with third parties for marketing or advertising purposes, but only with your explicit consent.

Security

We take the security of your personal information seriously and have implemented appropriate measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. We use industry-standard encryption and other security measures to protect your information, and we regularly review our security practices to ensure that your information is protected.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or to comply with legal or regulatory requirements. We will notify you of any changes to this Privacy Policy by posting the updated policy on our website and in the app.

Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or the information we collect, please contact us at talat@medassolutions.com

Effective Date: 17 January 2023
